I love the idea that anthros are culturally defiant. Not in the loud "gay pride parade" type of way but in the unfettered "This is how my mind works" kind of way. They don't try to blend in with other species, they make it a point to draw distinctions between species in order to exemplify their dope cultures. You can have a small group of lizards in a town full of foxes celebrating their own created holidays just to hold on to hope for the future, warmer winters, and bugs on the table.

Look, what I'm saying is, when an anthro marries a human, the children are going to lose a LOT of culture. You can celebrate all of the different holidays and both religions and speak lizard with human, if you mix it all together it's just too much and the child won't retain it all. What we need is a new merged culture. We need hmofa support networks where the kids can hang out, we need hmofa squares where bachelors and families alike can talk and play, and fishing trips where human dads can take their anthro sons out together. we need hmofa holidays, like a merging of old relics into a tradition that people can celebrate. If you're marrying a fox, you combine the human Easter with "The Great Egg Feast" as foxes typically celebrate in the spring. You make it work.

It'll be tough but this is what needs to be done to foster an environment where your children grow up thinking they're normal, instead of the weird outliers of interspecies couples.
